# Data Directory Structure

```
data/
├── chat-signals/        — Chat session signal extracts
├── meeting-signals/     — Meeting transcript → structured data
├── schedule-signals/    — Calendar/schedule events
├── normalized/          — Unified daily JSONL (all signals merged)
├── intel/               — Nightly analysis output (JSON)
├── pre-brief/           — Morning meeting prep dossiers
├── daily-snapshots/     — Daily direction snapshots
├── weekly-snapshots/    — Weekly synthesis
├── action-graphs/       — Meeting → action nodes
├── merged-signals/      — Rolling merged signals
├── identity-state/      — Personality/pattern state tracking
├── brain/               — entities.jsonl + aliases.jsonl (entity registry)
├── quality/             — Wiki quality gate reports
├── drift/               — Drift detection logs
├── voice-inbox/         — Voice memo inputs
└── saju-filter/         — Optional saju monthly filters
```

## Signal Flow
1. Raw signals land in `chat-signals/`, `meeting-signals/`, `schedule-signals/`, `voice-inbox/`
2. Normalized into `normalized/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl` (one line per signal)
3. Merged into `merged-signals/` for rolling state
4. Nightly intel agent reads merged → produces `intel/YYYY-MM-DD.json`
5. Wiki compiler reads intel → updates wiki pages
6. Morning agent reads intel + pre-brief + schedule → `daily-snapshots/`
7. Evening agent reads daily snapshot + signals → evening close
8. Weekly synthesis aggregates daily snapshots → `weekly-snapshots/`

## Entity Registry (`brain/`)
- `entities.jsonl`: one JSON object per line — `{"id", "slug", "category", "name", "created_at"}`
- `aliases.jsonl`: one JSON object per line — `{"alias", "entity_id"}`

## Quality & Drift
- `quality/`: wiki quality gate reports (explored ratio, bias check coverage, citation completeness)
- `drift/`: detects when wiki compiled truth diverges from recent signals
